<p>I'm working with LESS CSS to do loops and I would like to know how to set the transform property in loops.</p>  <pre><code>@from : 0; @to : 6;  .loop(@index) when(@index =&lt; @to) {      div:nth-child(@{index}) {         -webkit-transform: scale(@index * 0.1);         transform: scale(@index * 0.1);     }      .loop(@index + 1); }  .loop(@from); </code></pre>  <p>It should output something like this:</p>  <pre><code>div:nth-child(1) {     -webkit-transform: scale(.1);     transform: scale(.1); } div:nth-child(2) {     -webkit-transform: scale(.2);     transform: scale(.2); } div:nth-child(3) {     -webkit-transform: scale(.3);     transform: scale(.3); } div:nth-child(4) {     -webkit-transform: scale(.4);     transform: scale(.4); } div:nth-child(5) {     -webkit-transform: scale(.5);     transform: scale(.5); } </code></pre>